# Canvas & Node Conventions

All node-based canvases (ShawnderMind, Gemini Studio, Tool Editor, and any future tools)
MUST share the same interaction model, visual style, and design tokens.

## ReactFlow Config (required on every `<ReactFlow>`)

```tsx
<ReactFlow
  panOnDrag={[1]}
  selectionOnDrag
  selectionMode={SelectionMode.Partial}
  snapToGrid
  snapGrid={[20, 20]}
  fitView
  fitViewOptions={{ padding: 0.4 }}
  minZoom={0.2}
  colorMode="dark"
  proOptions={{ hideAttribution: true }}
>
  <Background variant={BackgroundVariant.Lines} gap={20} size={1} color="rgba(255,255,255,0.06)" />
  <Controls className="flow-controls" />
  <MiniMap className="flow-minimap" maskColor="rgba(0,0,0,0.6)" />
</ReactFlow>
```

## CSS Design Tokens (never hardcode hex)

Use shorthand aliases from `packages/ui/src/tokens.css`:

| Token                | Use for                       |
|----------------------|-------------------------------|
| `var(--bg-base)`     | Shell / page background       |
| `var(--bg-surface)`  | Node body, panels, sidebars   |
| `var(--bg-elevated)` | Input fields, cards, dropdowns|
| `var(--border)`      | All borders                   |
| `var(--accent)`      | Focus rings, active states    |
| `var(--text-primary)`| Main text                     |
| `var(--text-secondary)`| Labels, descriptions       |
| `var(--text-muted)`  | Hints, placeholders           |
| `var(--radius-sm)`   | Inputs, buttons (4px)         |
| `var(--radius-lg)`   | Node outer border (12px)      |
| `var(--shadow-node)` | Node drop shadow              |

## Node Styling Pattern

Every node must follow the BaseNode pattern from ShawnderMind:

- **Outer**: `background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);`
- **Width**: `min-width: 260px; max-width: 340px;`
- **Selection glow**: `border-color: <accent>; box-shadow: 0 0 16px <accent at 0.3 alpha>;`
- **Header**: uppercase, 12px, 700 weight, rounded top corners
- **Body padding**: `12px 14px`, flex column, `gap: 10px`
- **Handles**: `width: 12px; height: 12px; border: 2px solid var(--bg-surface);`

## Sidebar / ToolDock Pattern

- Background: `#111114` (matches ShawnderMind ToolDock)
- Border: `1px solid var(--border)`
- Shadow: `box-shadow: 4px 0 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4)`
- Section headers: `var(--text-muted)`, uppercase, 10-11px

## Edge Styling

All canvases must use the shared `PipelineEdge` component from `src/app/ideation/canvas/edges/PipelineEdge.tsx`:

```tsx
import PipelineEdge from '@/app/ideation/canvas/edges/PipelineEdge';
const edgeTypes: EdgeTypes = { pipeline: PipelineEdge };
// On <ReactFlow>:
edgeTypes={edgeTypes}
defaultEdgeOptions={{ type: 'pipeline' }}
```

For non-pipeline apps (Gemini Studio, Tool Editor), set `data: { isComplete: true }` on edges so they render as solid visible lines rather than dim dashed ones.

## Node Header Colors

Node headers must use **solid, opaque** background colors (matching the node's accent) — never semi-transparent gradients. Text on headers should be dark (`#0f0f1a`) for readability.

## Shared vs App-Specific Nodes

All apps should reuse the same base node components wherever possible. A node should only be app-specific if its behavior is fundamentally different in that context. Examples:
- **StartNode** — specific to ShawnderMind (depends on pipeline orchestrator)
- **BaseNode** — pattern to follow for all nodes across all apps
- **PipelineEdge** — shared across all apps

## ToolDock / Sidebar

All canvases must use the shared `ToolDock.css` classes from `src/app/ideation/canvas/ToolDock.css`. The dock must include:
- Tabs (Nodes + Details/Tools)
- Search bar
- Collapsible categories with icon, label, count, chevron
- Lock/Unlock pin button
- Full-height collapse strip

## Do NOT

- Use hardcoded hex colors for backgrounds, borders, or text — use tokens
- Use `BackgroundVariant.Dots` — always use `Lines`
- Omit `panOnDrag`, `selectionOnDrag`, `snapToGrid`, or `colorMode="dark"`
- Create custom Controls/MiniMap styles — use `flow-controls` / `flow-minimap` classes
- Use default React Flow edges — always use `PipelineEdge`
- Use semi-transparent gradient backgrounds on node headers
